{"word":"ἄφυκτος","slug":"ἄφυκτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄφυκτος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φεύγω'><el>φεύγω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>not to be shunned, from which none escape</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; of an arrow, <i>unerring</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; of a question, <i>admitting no escape, inevitable</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>unable to escape</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}